name: NonDocumentTypeChildNode
description: The NonDocumentTypeChildNode interface contains methods that are particular to Node objects that can have a parent, but not suitable for DocumentType.

members.name: NonDocumentTypeChildNode.previousElementSibling
members.description: Returns the Element immediately prior to this node in its parent's children list, or null if there is no Element in the list prior to this node.

members.name: NonDocumentTypeChildNode.nextElementSibling
members.description: Returns the Element immediately following this node in its parent's children list, or null if there is no Element in the list following this node.
